Package com.ibm.ecm.api.coresdk.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IBMECMAccessControlEntry
    Represents an access control entry object that is used to grant access to an item.
    IBMECMApplication
    Represents the main application or device interfacing with this SDK.
    IBMECMAttributeDefinition
    Represents the definition of an attribute, or property, for a class.
    IBMECMAuthenticator
    Represents the protocol that must be implemented for a custom authentication mechanism to be used by this framework.
    IBMECMAuthenticatorDataSource
    The data source that is used to inject a custom third-party authentication mechanism into this framework.
    IBMECMBaseObject
    Represents the base class that provides the id and name of an object, or item, that other items extend from.
    IBMECMBaseUser
    Represents the base class for IBMECMUser or IBMECMUserGroup.
    IBMECMComment
    Represents a single comment that is associated with a content item.
    IBMECMContentClass
    Represents a class definition or a metadata of a class.
    IBMECMContentItem
    Represents a single content item in the repository.
    IBMECMDesktop
    Represents an IBM Content Navigator desktop that the current application is accessing.
    IBMECMDirectory
    Represents a directory that stores users and groups.
    IBMECMFavorite
    Represents a favorite item in IBM Content Navigator.
    IBMECMItem
    Represents a base item that is contained in a repository.
    IBMECMItemProperty<V>
    Represents a single property value that is a member of an IBMECMItemProperties collection.
    IBMECMRepository
    Represents a repository managed in IBM Content Navigator.
    IBMECMSearchCriteria
    Represents a search criteria object in a search template IBMECMSearchTemplate.
    IBMECMSearchFolderSetting
    Represents one setting object for folder scope in one search template IBMECMSearchTemplate.
    IBMECMSearchPredicate
    Represents search predicates.
    IBMECMSearchPredicateBuilder
    Represents builder for IBMECMSearchPredicate.
    IBMECMSearchRepository
    Represents one target repository in search scope in a search template IBMECMSearchTemplate.
    IBMECMSearchResultDisplaySetting
    Represents a setting object for search result in one search template IBMECMSearchTemplate.
    IBMECMSearchTemplate
    Represents a search template object in IBM Content Navigator.
    IBMECMSearchTemplateBuilder
    A search template builder that builds a IBMECMSearchTemplate dynamically.
    IBMECMSocialItem
    References a social item such as comments, tags, recommendations (or likes), and download records.
    IBMECMSyncChange
    Represents a change that occurs on an item during a sync process.
    IBMECMSyncDevice  
    IBMECMSyncInfo  
    IBMECMSyncItem
    Represents an item that has been enabled for syncing.
    IBMECMTeamspace
    Represents a teamspace in IBM Content Navigator.
    IBMECMTeamspaceUserPermissions
    Represents the permission information for a user that has access to a teamspace.
    IBMECMTextSearchCriteria
    Represents a text search criteria object.
    IBMECMTextSearchPredicate
    Represents of text search predicates.
    IBMECMTextSearchPredicateBuilder
    Represents builder for IBMECMTextSearchPredicate.
    IBMECMUser
    Represents a repository user.
    IBMECMUserGroup
    Represents a group of users defined by the directory service.
    IBMECMUserRole
    Represents a role that users or groups can be assigned to.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    IBMECMCompletionHandler<T>
    This class processes results of asynchronous calls.
    IBMECMProgressListener
    A class that is used to listen for progress on an item that is being uploaded or downloaded from a server.
